      • not

        protected static <T> BiPredicate<T,T> not(BiPredicate<T,T> predicate)
        Negates a predicate. This is a utility method that simply returns predicate.negate(), and is equivalent to the static method that was added to Predicate in Java 11.

        This method can be used with method references. Example: not(LocalDate::isAfter).

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type to test.
        Parameters:
        predicate - The predicate to negate.
        Returns:
        The negated predicate.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given predicate is null.

      • plus

        protected static Instant plus(Instant instant,
                              TemporalAmount amount)
        Adds a TemporalAmount to an Instant.

        Unlike Instant.plus(TemporalAmount), this method supports not only Duration but also other TemporalAmounts like Period. If the TemporalAmount is not a Duration, this method first converts the Instant to a ZonedDateTime using ZoneId.systemDefault(), then adds the TemporalAmount, then converts the ZonedDateTime back to an Instant.

        Parameters:
        instant - The Instant to add a TemporalAmount to.
        amount - The TemporalAmount to add.
        Returns:
        The result of adding the TemporalAmount to the Instant.

      • minus

        protected static Instant minus(Instant instant,
                               TemporalAmount amount)
        Subtracts a TemporalAmount from an Instant.

        Unlike Instant.minus(TemporalAmount), this method supports not only Duration but also other TemporalAmounts like Period. If the TemporalAmount is not a Duration, this method first converts the Instant to a ZonedDateTime using ZoneId.systemDefault(), then subtracts the TemporalAmount, then converts the ZonedDateTime back to an Instant.

        Parameters:
        instant - The Instant to subtract a TemporalAmount from.
        amount - The TemporalAmount to subtract.
        Returns:
        The result of subtracting the TemporalAmount from the Instant.
